org.modelio.vcore.smkernel.mapi

Class MRef

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.modelio.vcore.smkernel.mapi.MRef
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class MRef
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    Model object reference.

    Allows to reference a model object that may or not be known. The reference is made of the object metaclass name, the object identifier and optionally the object name.

    See Also:

        public MRef(MObject element)
        Creates a reference for the given element.
        Beware that thes C'Tor accesses to the object name meaning that it might cause the effective 'loading in memory' of the whole MObject. To avoid this 'loading' see withoutName(MObject).

        public java.lang.String toString()

        • 'nnnn' = name

      • withoutName

        public static final MRef withoutName(MObject element)
        Creates a reference for the given element without loading the element name.

        Can be used to avoid loading a not yet loaded MObject or an object whose loading may fail with exception.

        Parameters:
        element - The element to reference.

      • toURIString

        public java.lang.String toURIString()
        Return a "mref:" opaque URI like string for this MRef.
        An opaque URI is an absolute URI whose scheme-specific part does not begin with a slash character ('/'). The build URI String is "mref:metaclass/uuid/name"
        Returns:
        an opaque URI or null in case of syntax error.
        Since:
        5.2.0
